informal_statement:
Let $n$ be the smallest positive integer satisfying the following system of congruences:
  \begin{align*}
  n &\equiv 2 \pmod{3} \\
  n &\equiv 3 \pmod{5} \\
  n &\equiv 1 \pmod{7}
  \end{align*}
  Then $n = 8$.

